  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Outlet Manager",
  "description": "<p>Job Description</p><ul><li>At all times, to keep the clinic/beauty salon organized, clean, and attractive to customers.</li><li>To oversee the clinic/beauty salon sales team and other staff members. This includes supervising employees, delegating tasks, evaluating employee performance, managing staff problems, and designing work schedules.</li><li>Oversee the clinic’s/beauty salon's inventory by maintaining stock and purchasing new supplies as needed.</li><li>To greet incoming customers, answer phone calls, and address customer complaints. When customers are ready to check out, assistant outlet managers supervise the cashier to complete sales and collect payments.</li><li>To achieve assigned target and goals set by company.</li><li>Ensure cohesive and harmonious working environment at all level in order to achieve Staff Retention rate.</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>At least 1 year proven experience in managing a clinic/beauty salon or similar role</li><li>Knowledge of the best practices for running a clinic/beauty salon</li><li>Ability to handle customers' requests and complaints with grace</li><li>Sales oriented and customer focus</li><li>Professionalism, independent and initiative with strong self-motivation</li><li>Excellent communication skills </li><li>Positive thinking and attitude</li><li>Ability to establish effective policies and procedures, and maintain high service delivery standards</li></ul>",
